<div class='page-break'></div>
<div class='preliminary-header'>ABSTRACT</div>
<br/>
<p>
  This project focuses on developing a Web-Based Job Portal System, named CareerHub, to address the challenges of manual job application tracking, layout white spaces, and lack of visual alignment in existing digital employment portals. Traditional systems often lead to visual clutter, high cognitive load, and poor usability, making it difficult for both job seekers to search for roles and employers to screen candidate submissions.
</p>
<p>
  To solve this problem, a computerized, fully responsive MERN application was designed and developed to automate key recruitment operations such as resume submission, job posting management, user registration, and role-based dashboard visualization. The system provides an interactive, dark-mode-equipped interface that optimizes visual balance and significantly reduces candidate screening workloads.
</p>
<p>
  The project was developed using a modern technology stack consisting of React.js, Tailwind CSS, and Framer Motion for the front-end, with Node.js, Express.js, and MongoDB used for back-end API development and database management. These technologies were selected for their responsive rendering speeds, component scalability, and efficient data serialization.
</p>
<p>
  As an outcome, the system successfully improves visual engagement, eliminates background contrasts, and provides seamless real-time theme toggling across dashboards. It also enables recruiters to view, review, and filter applicants efficiently. This project demonstrates how modern SPA architectures and sleek UI design systems can significantly improve the online recruitment experience.
</p>
