<h1>CHAPTER 5: IMPLEMENTATION</h1>
<br/>
<h2>5.1 Programming Languages Used</h2>
<ul>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>JavaScript (ES6+)</span>: The primary programming language used for both front-end component state management and backend API routing.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>HTML5 & CSS3</span>: Used for document structuring, styled overlays, and theme variables mapping.
  </li>
</ul>
<h2>5.2 Tools and Technologies</h2>
<p>
  The application utilizes the following development tools:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><span class='bold'>Vite</span>: A build tool that compiles front-end modules quickly and supports Hot Module Replacement (HMR).</li>
  <li><span class='bold'>ExpressJS</span>: The backend framework that processes stateless REST APIs and serves file uploads.</li>
  <li><span class='bold'>MongoDB & Mongoose</span>: Used for storing user data schemas and querying them using Javascript models.</li>
  <li><span class='bold'>Tailwind CSS (v4)</span>: Extends class-based utility styles (e.g., custom border overlays and gradients).</li>
</ul>
<h2>5.3 Key Features</h2>
<p>
  CareerHub implements several unique quality enhancements:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>Global Theme Context</span>: A state engine ([ThemeContext.jsx](file:///c:/Users/USER/JOBPORTAL_fixed/frontend/CareerHub/src/context/ThemeContext.jsx)) that toggles '.dark' class attributes on 'document.documentElement' and stores preferences in 'localStorage'.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>Tactile Dashboard Animations</span>: Uses Framer Motion to animate sidebar highlights, page entries, and hover states.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>Glassmorphic Search Header</span>: Replaced solid light headers with transparent panels ('bg-white/80 dark:bg-slate-900/85 backdrop-blur-sm').
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>Dark WebKit Scrollbar</span>: Customized scrollbars inside CSS to match the slate-950 theme.
  </li>
</ul>
<h2>5.4 Code Structure</h2>
<p>
  The MERN architecture directory is organized as follows:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>/backend</span>: Containing 'server.js' (entry point), '/controllers' (business logic), '/models' (mongoose schemas), and '/routes' (express routers).
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>/frontend/CareerHub/src</span>:
    <ul>
      <li>'/components/layout': Contains common UI wrappers ('Navbar.jsx', 'ThemeToggle.jsx', 'DashboardLayout.jsx').</li>
      <li>'/context': Contains user authenticators ('AuthContext.jsx') and theme engines ('ThemeContext.jsx').</li>
      <li>'/pages': Contains routing pages divided into '/Auth', '/Employer', '/JobSeeker', '/Admin'.</li>
      <li>'index.css': The master stylesheet containing CSS overrides and dark mode rules.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<h2>5.5 GUI Layouts</h2>
<p>
  The responsive GUI pages are verified to load correctly:
</p>
<ol>
  <li><span class='bold'>Landing Page</span>: Features a 2-column layout with a visual stats mockup on the right to balance whitespace.</li>
  <li><span class='bold'>Auth Forms (Login/SignUp)</span>: Clean, centered form cards over a dot-grid background.</li>
  <li><span class='bold'>Recruiter Panel</span>: Features application viewer cards with resume download links and active status toggles.</li>
</ol>
<div class='page-break'></div>
<h1>CHAPTER 6: TESTING & EVALUATION</h1>
<br/>
<h2>6.1 Test Plan</h2>
<p>
  The test plan is designed to verify system integrity across all major features. Testing focuses on verifying the role-based views (Job Seeker, Employer, Admin) and theme toggles.
</p>
<h2>6.2 Test Cases (Table Format)</h2>
<p>
  Below is the test execution matrix:
</p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>TC_ID</th>
      <th>Feature Description</th>
      <th>Input Test Vector</th>
      <th>Expected Output Outcome</th>
      <th>Status</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td class='bold'>TC_01</td>
      <td>User Registration</td>
