</table>
<h2>6.3 Types of Testing</h2>
<ul>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>Unit Testing</span>: Tested independent helper modules (e.g., date formatting in helper.js and token decoders in auth context) to ensure correct outputs.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>Integration Testing</span>: Verified the MERN communication flow: verifying that React frontend submissions successfully reached Express routers, modified MongoDB records, and returned clean JSON responses.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>Black-box Testing</span>: Verified user authentication and job filter updates from the browser UI without direct database manipulation.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>White-box Testing</span>: Inspected routing logic to ensure that only authenticated recruiters have access to candidate profiles.
  </li>
</ul>
<h2>6.4 Results and Analysis</h2>
<p>
  All 10 test cases executed successfully without failures. The MERN backend responded to queries within expected thresholds, and the CSS classes automatically adapted to the active theme. Disabling all box shadows in dark mode solved the white halo bug, and custom scrollbars integrated perfectly.
</p>
<div class='page-break'></div>
<h1>CHAPTER 7: CONCLUSION & FUTURE WORK</h1>
<br/>
<h2>7.1 Summary of the Project</h2>
<p>
  The CareerHub Job Portal project was successfully designed, implemented, and verified. By utilizing the MERN stack combined with modern Tailwind CSS variables, the application provides a fast, responsive online recruitment experience. Key visual enhancements—such as centered auth cards, dot-grid backdrops, transparent glass headers, and custom dark scrollbars—resolved layout issues and significantly improved the user experience.
</p>
<h2>7.2 Achievements</h2>
<p>
  The project achieved the following key milestones:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Implemented a system-wide theme toggler with persistent state tracking in local browser storage.</li>
  <li>Redesigned the Landing page into a balanced, 2-column responsive layout.</li>
  <li>Created modern form card wrappers and dot-grid backdrops for Login, SignUp, and password recovery pages.</li>
  <li>Polished the Recruiting Overview screen and candidate list panels for a clean layout in both light and dark modes.</li>
  <li>Verified that the client application builds cleanly for production.</li>
</ul>
<h2>7.3 Limitations</h2>
<p>
  Due to project timeline constraints, the following limitations remain:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Lack of interactive data charts on dashboards.</li>
  <li>No built-in resume parser to extract candidate skills automatically.</li>
  <li>No live chat client between recruiters and applicants.</li>
</ul>
<h2>7.4 Suggestions for Future Improvements</h2>
<p>
  To transition CareerHub into a commercial-grade product, future work should prioritize:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>Dashboard Charts Integration</span>: Using libraries like Recharts to render monthly application metrics.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>In-App PDF Previews</span>: Using react-pdf to let recruiters preview resumes side-by-side inside the profile modal.
  </li>
  <li>
    <span class='bold'>Rich Text Input</span>: Replacing plain text description fields with WYSIWYG editors (e.g., React Quill) for formatted job listings.
  </li>
</ol>
